-- Eczacibasi of Turkey Purchases 50% of Power Producer Erguvan
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-02-06T09:55:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/eczacibasi-of-turkey-purchases-50-of-power-producer-erguvan.html
Eczacibasi Holding AS (0111222D) , a Turkish
company with interest in pharmaceuticals and building materials,
bought a 50 percent stake in Turkish power producer Erguvan
Enerji Elektrik Uretim AS, the country’s antitrust body said.  The purchase doesn’t violate competition rules, the
watchdog said on  its website . Eczacibasi bought the stake in
Erguvan from Yalcin Erol Demirer and Onder Demirer, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
